gnetGetGlobalTable 
 char *gnetGetGlobalTable(const char *cssTableName)
Get a global table filename. Get the name of the file currently being used for a global CSS table. Returns NULL, if no table file exits. The default location of a global file is $GEOTOOL_HOME/tables/static/global.cssTableName. Use gnetSetGlobalTable to override this default with another filename.

Parameters:
cssTableName - The name of the table.
Returns:
the filename. Do not free.

gnetReadGlobalTable 
 int gnetReadGlobalTable(const char *cssTableName,
                         Vector v)
Read a global table. The default location for all global tables is $GEOTOOL_HOME/tables/static/cssTableName. Use the routine gnetSetGlobalTable to override the default location before calling this routine. This routine returns 0, if a global file is not found in the default directory, and an alternative location has not been set. It returns 1, if the file is found and successfully read. It returns -1, if an error occurs while opening or reading the file.

Parameters:
v - A vector to receive the CssTable objects.
Returns:
-1, 0, or 1.

gnetSetGlobalTable 
 int gnetSetGlobalTable(const char *cssTableName,
                        const char *path)
Set a global table filename. Set the name of a global table file that will be read whenever tables of that type are requested. Overrides the default location $GEOTOOL_HOME/tables/static/global.cssTableName.

Parameters:
cssTableName - The name of the table.
path - The name of the table file.
Returns:
0 for success, -1 for an error.
